rComments: She is INCREDIBLY knowledgeable in economics, specifically in the health field. Unfortunately she makes this course VERY econ dominant and expects you to remember & apply complex econ terms & formulas. She isn't clear on her expectations & grading criteria, but ridicules you if asked to clarify on math terminology you haven't used since highschool.
Fantastic professor, her class got me into economics. Very energetic and wants you to succeed, Catherine is one of the best Econ teachers at Ottawa U.

I love microeconomics to death, but professor Armstrong makes me want to quit. She rarely has any idea of what shes doing in class, often making mistakes on her explanations and wasting time to redo everything again. She teaches very slowly but its good if you dont want to open a book to study. Her exams are fairly easy, at least.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']
